rawData.description: EPISUITE Estimation Programs Interface Suite™ is a Windows®-based suite of physical/chemical property and environmental fate estimation programs developed by EPA’s and Syracuse Research Corp.

The NICEATM workflow is a program which provides QSAR/QSPR model predictions and assessment of applicability domains. The models are built on curated data from the public domain as described in our publication (http://pubs.acs.org/doi/abs/10.1021/acs.jcim.6b00625). Molecular descriptors were calculated using PaDEL software and a variety of machine learning algorithms were used to model the data. Winning models were chosen based on accuracy against external test sets.

OPERA is a free and open source/open data suite of QSAR Models providing predictions and additional information including applicability domain and accuracy assessment, as described in the publication OPERA models for predicting physicochemical properties and environmental fate endpoints. All models were built on curated data and standardized chemical structures as described in the publication An automated curation procedure for addressing chemical errors and inconsistencies in public datasets used in QSAR modelling. All OPERA properties are predicted under ambient conditions of 760mm of Hg at 25 degrees Celsius.
ACD/Labs physicochemical properties are predicted by the ACD/Labs Percepta Platform.

OPERA is a free and open source/open data suite of QSAR Models providing predictions and additional information including applicability domain and accuracy assessment, as described in the publication OPERA models for predicting physicochemical properties and environmental fate endpoints. All models were built on curated data and standardized chemical structures as described in the publication An automated curation procedure for addressing chemical errors and inconsistencies in public datasets used in QSAR modelling. All OPERA properties are predicted under ambient conditions of 760mm of Hg at 25 degrees Celsius.

The PHYSPROP data sets are the publicly available data files underpinning the EPISuiteTM prediction models.  The data were curated by NCCT using a combination of manual and automated processing routines with only the highest quality data reported.

The Toxicity Estimation Software Tool (TEST) is an EPA software application developed to allow users to easily estimate the toxicity of chemicals using Quantitative Structure Activity Relationships (QSARs) methodologies.
